└── Package.swift
```

## Module boundaries

| Module | Owns | Does NOT own |
|--------|------|--------------|
| `DiskScannerKit` | Volume crawl, classification, scan persistence | UI, duplicate hashing |
| `MetadataKit` | AVFoundation/ImageIO metadata extraction | File deletion |
| `DuplicateKit` | Filename/size/hash/video fingerprint detection | Cleanup execution |
| `CleanupKit` | Preview + Trash workflow | Permanent deletion by default |
| `AIKit` | Insights, recommendations, optional Ollama reports | Cloud AI / data exfiltration |
| `DatabaseKit` | GRDB schema, migrations, queries | Business UI logic |

## Technology stack

| Layer | Choice |
|-------|--------|
| Language | Swift |
| UI | SwiftUI + Swift Charts |
| IDE | VS Code (primary) + Xcode (build/sign/archive) |
| Database | SQLite + GRDB |
| AI | Rule-based analysis + optional local Ollama |
| Distribution | Xcode Archive + Notarization + DMG |

## Cleanup safety

- Default destructive action: **Move to Trash** via `FileManager.trashItem`
- Always preview before cleanup; never delete without explicit user confirmation
- Grant Full Disk Access only when needed; explain why in UI

## Agent conventions

1. **Minimal diff** — match existing Swift/SwiftUI patterns; no drive-by refactors.
2. **Docs** — cross-cutting updates go in `docs/` or `README.md`.
3. **Performance** — scans are I/O heavy; use background queues, cancellation, incremental UI updates.
4. **Privacy** — all analysis on-device; no path/content upload unless user adds sync explicitly.
5. **Testing** — XCTest for scanners, classifiers, duplicate helpers, and database layer.

## Phased scope

| Phase | Scope |
|-------|--------|
| **Phase 1** | Disk scanning, folder analysis, duplicate detection, cleanup |
| **Phase 2** | AI recommendations, large media analysis, duplicate videos |
| **Phase 3** | Storage trends, scheduled scans, NAS/SMB/Synology |
| **Phase 4** | Local LLM integration (Ollama / LM Studio) |

Do not implement Phase 3 NAS/enterprise features unless explicitly requested.

